radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated and fluid-filled measuring up to 1.2 cm in diameter with surrounding stranding. There is a focus of air surrounding the posterior margin of the inflamed appendix, likely representing air within an adjacent bowel loop. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenals, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, rectum, urinary bladder, and reproductive organs are unremarkable. No evidence of focal lesions or significant abnormalities was found in the visualized structures.
